@page "/blog/ec"

<PageTitle>Armenian Encoding Converter - NOSTDLIB</PageTitle>

<Navbar />

<article class="blog-post">
    <div class="container">
        <a href="/blog" class="back-link">&larr; Back to Blog</a>

        <header class="post-header">
            <span class="post-icon">🔤</span>
            <h1>[EC] Armenian Encoding Converter</h1>
            <div class="post-meta">
                <span class="post-tech mono">C#, .NET 9</span>
                <span class="post-status beta">Beta</span>
            </div>
            <p class="post-intro">A .NET 9 application designed to convert Armenian text between different encoding formats, featuring a core library, CLI, and GUI (in development).</p>
        </header>

        <section class="post-section">
            <h2>Overview</h2>
            <p>
                The Armenian Encoding Converter (EC) addresses the challenge of working with Armenian text across different encoding systems.
                Whether you're dealing with legacy ANSI-encoded documents or modern Unicode text, EC provides a robust solution for seamless conversion.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="post-section">
            <h2>Key Features</h2>
            <div class="features-grid">
                <div class="feature-item">
                    <h3>TextConverter</h3>
                    <p>Handles text transformation via mapping files</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-item">
                    <h3>ExcelConverter</h3>
                    <p>Processes spreadsheets (Windows/Office required)</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-item">
                    <h3>WordConverter</h3>
                    <p>Manages document conversion (Windows/Office required)</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-item">
                    <h3>EncodingMapper</h3>
                    <p>Loads character mappings from configuration files</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="post-section">
            <h2>System Requirements</h2>
            <ul class="requirements-list">
                <li>.NET 9 SDK</li>
                <li>Windows OS (for Word/Excel conversion)</li>
                <li>Microsoft Office (for document/spreadsheet conversion)</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="post-section">
            <h2>Getting Started</h2>
            <p>Clone the repository and build the project:</p>
            <pre class="code-block"><code>git clone https://github.com/mrzaxaryan/EC.git
cd EC
dotnet build
dotnet test</code></pre>
        </section>

        <section class="post-section">
            <h2>CLI Usage</h2>
            <p>The application supports two conversion directions via command-line:</p>
            <pre class="code-block"><code>dotnet run --project EC.CLI -- --file &lt;path&gt; --type &lt;0|1&gt;</code></pre>
            <ul class="param-list">
                <li><code>--type 0</code> — ANSI to Unicode</li>
                <li><code>--type 1</code> — Unicode to ANSI</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Supported formats: Word (.doc, .docx) and Excel (.xls, .xlsx) files.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="post-section">
            <h2>Configuration</h2>
            <p>Character mappings are stored in <code>armenian.map</code> located at <code>EC/Encodings/armenian.map</code>.</p>
            <p>The mapping file uses a simple key-value format:</p>
            <pre class="code-block"><code># Comments start with #
A=Ա
B=Բ
...</code></pre>
        </section>

        <section class="post-section">
            <h2>Project Structure</h2>
            <div class="structure-grid">
                <div class="structure-item">
                    <h4>EC.Library</h4>
                    <p>Core functionality with converters and mapping capabilities</p>
                </div>
                <div class="structure-item">
                    <h4>EC.CLI</h4>
                    <p>Command-line tool for batch or single-file conversions</p>
                </div>
                <div class="structure-item">
                    <h4>EC.GUI</h4>
                    <p>Cross-platform graphical interface (in development)</p>
                </div>
                <div class="structure-item">
                    <h4>EC.Library.Tests</h4>
                    <p>Unit test suite for core logic</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="post-section">
            <h2>Limitations</h2>
            <ul class="limitations-list">
                <li>Word/Excel conversion requires Microsoft Office installed</li>
                <li>The mapping configuration file must exist at the expected location</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="post-section post-footer">
            <h2>Source Code</h2>
            <p>The project is open source under the MIT License.</p>
            <a href="https://github.com/mrzaxaryan/EC" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn btn-primary">
                View on GitHub
            </a>
        </section>
    </div>
</article>

<Footer />
